title: Olympic National Park: Coastal Cleanups
body: Explore This Park    Get Involved     Volunteer     Coastal Cleanups              Coastal Cleanups        Hundreds of volunteers take to the beaches of Washington State, including Olympic NP, to remove and dispose of marine debris. This event began as a park event and has expanded over time to include nearly all of the state's Pacific Coast.    Register to cleanup a beach at www.coastsavers.org
